properties.Name: Aircraft
properties.Description:
Most commonly used term for airplane.

An individual airplane or aircraft owned by the Carrier.

Columns.Name: AircraftId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Aircraft.

Columns.Name: AircraftSerialNumber
Columns.Description: The serial number assigned to the aircraft.

Columns.Name: AircraftTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Product.

Columns.Name: AircraftTypeConfigurationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Aircraft Type Configuration.

Columns.Name: AircraftOrderDate
Columns.Description: The date that the aircraft was ordered.

Columns.Name: AircraftManufactureStartDate
Columns.Description: The date that the aircraft manufacture process started.

Columns.Name: AircraftManufactureEndDate
Columns.Description: The date that the aircraft manufacture process ended.

Columns.Name: AircraftDeliveryDate
Columns.Description: The date that the aircraft was delivered.

Columns.Name: AircraftCertificationDate
Columns.Description: The date that the aircraft was certified.

Columns.Name: FirstOperationDate
Columns.Description: The first operational date of the aircraft.

Columns.Name: LastLightMaintenanceDate
Columns.Description: The last light maintenance performed date.

Columns.Name: LastHeavyMaintenanceDate
Columns.Description: The last heavy maintenance performed date.

Columns.Name: LastAvionicsMaintenanceDate
Columns.Description: The last avionics maintenance performed date.

Columns.Name: LastRegularlyScheduledMaintenanceDate
Columns.Description: The last regularly scheduled maintenance performed date.

Columns.Name: NoiseCertificationType
Columns.Description: The type of noise certification that the aircraft has

Columns.Name: NumberOfFlightdeckCrewMembers
Columns.Description: The number of flightdeck crew.

Columns.Name: NumberOfServiceCrewMembers
Columns.Description: The number of service crew.

Columns.Name: AllowableCabinLoad
Columns.Description: The maximum payload weight that can be carried on an airplane on a specific route segment under a specific set of operation conditions.

Columns.Name: StretchAircraftIndicator
Columns.Description: Aircraft like B-727-200 and B-737-300

Columns.Name: HighCapacityAircraftIndicator
Columns.Description: High Capacity Airplane    Equivalent to wide-bodied airplanes.  Specifically refers to B747, B767, B777, A300, A330, A340, DC10, MD-11, L-1011, IL-86 & IL-96.

Columns.Name: AirlineId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Airline.

Columns.Name: AssetId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Asset.

Columns.Name: OwningPartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.
